    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="118"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.019 EAC/6–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-22T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 22, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 22—3:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6315. Cornea 296. For Erhardt. US delegation EAC has studied intensively Gen
                    McNarney’s recommendations rearrangements for Vienna (urtel 4933, June 19<note
                        n="73" xml:id="d118fn73">Not printed</note>) and consulted Generals Flory
                    and Snavely in detail. Preliminary consultation UK delegation showed Brit
                    intention introduce several subsidiary issues all requiring reference to Moscow.
                    Prolonged consultations UK and French delegations reduced principal new issue to
                    provision of 3 airdromes.</p>
                <pb facs="0161" n="151" xml:id="pg_151"/>
                <p>Today Mosely made detailed review Austrian issues with Soviet delegation. Soviet
                    delegation referring to Moscow tonight proposal for 3 airdromes. EAC meeting
                        Saturday<note n="74" xml:id="d118fn74">June 23</note> morning on
                    Austria.</p>
                <p>Sent to Dept as 6315; rptd AusPolAd as 5.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
